          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 8 3/8 in. by 5 3/8, consisting of 30 leaves, some
                                    of which are much stained and torn, especially foll. 2, 14, 15,
                                    23—26, and 28. The quires are signed with arithmetical figures
                                    (fol. 15 a, <foreign xml:lang="ar">٢٢</foreign>). Leaves are wanting at the beginning, and after
                                    foll. 1, 7, 22, 26, 27, and 28. There are from 20 to 25 lines in
                                    each page. </p>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <extent>
                           <measure type="composition" unit="leaf" quantity="30">30 ff.</measure>
                        </extent>
                        <condition>
                           <list>
                              <item>
                                 <p>Vellum, about 8 3/8 in. by 5 3/8, consisting of 30 leaves, some
                                    of which are much stained and torn, especially foll. 2, 14, 15,
                                    23—26, and 28. The quires are signed with arithmetical figures
                                    (fol. 15 a, %). Leaves are wanting at the beginning, and after
                                    foll. 1, 7, 22, 26, 27, and 28. There are from 20 to 25 lines in
                                    each page. </p>
                              </item>
                           </list>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="3">
              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" medium="unknown" scope="major" script="syr-Syre">
                The greater part of this volume (foll. 1—22) is written in a fine,
                regular Esṭrangělā of the <date calendar="Gregorian" notBefore="0500" notAfter="0600">vith cent</date>.</handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote2" medium="unknown" scope="minor" script="syr">
                The remainder (foll. 23—30) is in a less elegant and somewhat later
                  hand.</handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote3" medium="unknown" scope="minor" script="syr">
                <ref target="#addition1">See additions.</ref> 
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <additions>
              <note type="proofreader-note">N.B., folio location may not be available for some items below.</note>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <p>On fol. 30 a, at the foot of the page, a reader called
                                 <persName>Sergius</persName> has recorded his name.</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܐܠܗܐ ܚܣܐ ܠܥܒܕܟ ܣܪܓܝܣ ܒܨܠܘܬ ܡܪܝ ܓܘܪܓܝܣ ܐܡܝܢ</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <locus from="30b" to="30b"/>
                  <p>In Coptic, the name
                              of one "<persName>Mercurius the sinner</persName>."</p>
                  <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="cop">
                                ⲙⲉⲣⲕⲟⲩⲣⲩ ⲡⲓⲣⲉϥⲉⲣⲛⲟⲃⲓ
                    </quote>
                           </p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
